OL,7,FHe had urged the judge not to impose a
OL,8,Fnon-harassment order, saying it would
OL,9,F"sever the relationship" with the
OL,10,Fchild.
OL,12,F"The verdict of the jury was that the
OL,13,Fmental condition of the accused was
OL,14,Fnot such that the statutory defence
OL,15,Fwas made out," Mr Allan said.
OL,17,F"What the jury didn't do was say that
OL,18,Fhe wasn't suffering from some kind of
OL,19,Fdepressive condition."
